  "prompt": "What is Shaoxing vinegar used for?",
  "response": "Shaoxing vinegar is a key ingredient in Chinese cuisine, particularly in Zhejiang province. It is a dark brown rice vinegar with a complex, slightly sweet, and mildly acidic flavor. Some common uses include:\n\n1. Cooking\n- Marinades\n- Braising meats\n- Stir-fry sauces\n- Dipping sauces\n\n2. Flavoring dishes\n- Adding depth to soups\n- Seasoning dumplings\n- Enhancing cold appetizers\n\n3. Dipping sauces\n- Used in combination with soy sauce and other ingredients\n- Popular for dipping dumplings and other dim sum\n\n4. Traditional medicine\n- Believed to have health benefits in Chinese medicine\n- Used for digestion and other health purposes\n\n5. Pickling\n- Used in pickling vegetables and other foods\n\nShaoxing vinegar is distinct from other rice vinegars and is prized for its unique flavor profile in Chinese cooking.",
